social_posts.post_text: Back in 2015 this OG Ali called me to his cell to tell me his story after heard about mine. Now he’s serving a 60 year sentence and 56 years old at the time. He told me to utilize my time wisely focus on changing my mindset and put a positive plan together so I don’t end up like him serving a long sentence. He made sure I took this picture with him so I can never forget him! #streetz2fitness

social_posts.post_text: From prison to now, the only thing that kept me going was consistency! A strong mindset, desire to improve my life and self discipline is what fueled me. Self discipline is not taught it’s learned by creating a routine, repetition over and over and sticking to it no matter how bored or burnt out you may get. If you cannot stay committed to a routine you will never see the full potential of you mind and body! You have to go through a mental mindset transformation all the bs excuses will never benefit you anything but a step closer to being more unhealthy mentally, emotionally, and physically, in order to see your body transform self discipline is required! Retrain your mindset and stop making excuses!

Drop a comment if you can see @lilpump abs! 

Online coaching launching soon💪
Monday’s dictates the monument and sets the tone for the week!! Start off strong 💪🏽

After years of training while in prison I developed a strong mindset to push through my workouts even on the tough days when I felt unmotivated and depressed! Motivation was never a factor! Working out in prison is not fun I had to rely on self discipline to keep me going. Becoming the best version of myself and taking control of my life is what fueled me to go hard everyday! I always committed to working out with “the toughest” guys because I knew they would call me out and hold me accountable if I tried to make excuses!! Over time I developed enough self discipline to hold myself accountable and that’s when I knew I had become a leader and gained respect from other prisoners to follow my lead and join my workout crew. At that point I knew I discovered my passion and started walking in my purpose while inside and helped inmates get in shape! That’s why I became a personal trainer!!
Evolve so hard they have to get to know you again!

Consistency says a lot about your commitment! Dedication and hard work leads to results 💪

Dear Mama,
Sorry for disappointing you by traveling down the wrong path when I was younger, and not achieving the goals you had for me to graduate from Georgetown University like you! I had dreams of being like Allen Iverson playing for Georgetown. But I gave up on that dream… My life has been a tough rocky road navigating through life without you! I only met 2 of your sisters and a few of my cousins on your side, I never met 2 of your sisters nor your brother! I always wonder why? I guess it’s because I am bi-racial they did not want to accept or meet me. 2 of your sisters wrote me letters and sent me cards while I was in prison. Your best friend, my God Mother and God Father was there for me financially during my upbringing with my Great Aunt, and while I was in prison as well.  But I haven’t seen them since I was 14. I wish your sisters would’ve tried harder to adopt me when I was younger. I had dreams of being a basketball player or football player. I asked your sister could I come live her, she said yes! I was so excited to move to Chicago and play basketball but unfortunately my Great Aunt said no!! When I arrive back to Florida My Great Aunt told me they didn’t want me when I was little because they’re racist and I am black and they did not want me after you passed away. Then I found out I was being told lies, when I found out my Aunt adopted a black kid. I was so I felt cheated and robbed of a better life. I was manipulated and lied to my entire life!! But mom I want you to know this is not a justification for my actions. I am sorry for my past behavior and I hope you are proud of me now! Happy birthday I love you and I miss you! Sorry it took me so long to finally come visit you 🙏 

God thank you for blessing me with 3 guardian angels to protect me on my life journey!
